c: 7
v: 43
t: "We will strip away any rancor [that lingers] in their breasts. Rivers will flow beneath them and they will say: \"Praise be to God Who led us to this! We would never have been guided if God had not led us on. Our Lord´s messengers have brought the Truth.\" They will hear someone call out: \"Here is the Garden you have inherited because of what you have done"